video.title: Pokémon the Series: Sun & Moon
video.synopsis: Ash and his Pikachu travel to the Alola region with his mother and enroll in the Pokémon school, where they confront the nefarious Team Skull.

episodes.synopsis: During their Alolan vacation, Ash, Pikachu and Ash's mother encounter new Pokémon and deliver a Pokémon egg from Professor Oak to the Pokémon School.
episodes.title: Alola to New Adventure!

episodes.synopsis: Ash and Pikachu start classes at the Pokémon School with Professor Kukui and their new classmates, who are impressed by Ash's Z-Ring.
episodes.title: The Guardian’s Challenge!

episodes.synopsis: Team Rocket arrives in Alola. Professor Kukui gives Ash a Rotom Pokédex that can speak and interact with humans, and Ash heads out to catch Pokémon.
episodes.title: Loading the Dex!

episodes.synopsis: Ash and Pikachu's failure to capture a wild Alolan Pokémon results in a visit to the Pokémon Center. Team Rocket meets a Mimikyu and a Bewear.
episodes.title: First Catch in Alola, Ketchum-Style!

episodes.synopsis: The class takes an ocean field trip to help the water Pokémon train, and Popplio practices blowing bubbles. Team Rocket heads to the beach too.
episodes.title: Yo, Ho, Ho! Go, Popplio!

episodes.synopsis: Alone in the house for the day, Ash and his Pokémon friends struggle with domestic tasks, including laundry, cooking and grocery shopping.
episodes.title: A Shocking Grocery Run!

episodes.synopsis: Ash meets a wild Litten on the way to school; it takes advantage of his kindness by stealing his lunch and running away, and he decides to catch it.
episodes.title: That's Why the Litten is a Scamp!

episodes.synopsis: The class receives a Pokémon egg to care for as an assignment, and Lillie agrees to take care of the egg to get over her fear of handling Pokémon.
episodes.title: Lillie's Egg-xhilirating Challenge!

episodes.synopsis: Hala, the kahuna of Melemele Island, gives Ash his first Island Trials task: solve an infestation of Raticate and Rattata peacefully.
episodes.title: To Top a Totem!

episodes.synopsis: Ash prepares for his first Island Trial, in which he must defeat Hala, who's skilled with fighting-type Pokémon and who also has his own Z-Moves.
episodes.title: Trial and Tribulation!

episodes.synopsis: Ash and Pikachu visit Kiawe's family dairy farm on Akala Island, where there are lots of Pokémon and lots of chores to help with.
episodes.title: Young Kiawe Had a Farm!

episodes.synopsis: Ash and his classmates go on a field trip to the ocean. Little do they know that Team Rocket is there too, hunting for more Pokémon.
episodes.title: The Sun, The Scare, The Secret Lair!

episodes.synopsis: Ash decides to enter the Great Alola Pancake Race along with Pikachu. They're up against last year's champion and her Alolan Raichu.
episodes.title: Racing To A Big Event!

episodes.synopsis: The two Pokémon eggs hatch into Vulpixes: Lillie's is an Alolan type that she names Snowy. She and her Pokémon now have to get to know one another.
episodes.title: Getting to Know You!

episodes.synopsis: When Ash and Professor Kukui notice Rockruff coming home injured, they install surveillance cameras -- and learn that Rockruff is training in secret!
episodes.title: Rocking Clawmark Hill

episodes.synopsis: Lana's Popplio and Ash's Rowlet are blown away in one of Popplio's balloons. While Ash and Lana search for them, they fall straight into Team Rocket!
episodes.title: They Might Not Be Giants!

episodes.synopsis: When Ash loses his Z Crystal, Rotom takes the chance to imitate the detective on his favorite TV show, with Pikachu assisting him on the case.
episodes.title: Crystal-Clear Sleuthing!

episodes.synopsis: Ash helps Mallow search for a legendary ingredient so she can recreate a traditional Alolan recipe, but Team Rocket is also on the prowl.
episodes.title: A Seasoned Search!

episodes.synopsis: Ash realizes that he may be facing Tapu Koko in a rematch soon, so Sophocles offers to help out with scientific research for his training.
episodes.title: A Guardian Rematch!

episodes.synopsis: After hearing stories about "Treasure Island" from his friends, Ash sets off to explore the island with Pikachu and comes across a mysterious sight.
episodes.title: Partner Promises!

episodes.synopsis: Ash runs into Litten and its friend Stoutland again on his way home. When he learns Stoutland is ill, Ash takes it to the Pokémon Center.
episodes.title: One Journey Ends, Another Begins!

episodes.synopsis: Ash spots a strange little shovel moving around by itself during a training session. According to Kiawe, touching a Sandygast’s shovel means trouble.
episodes.title: A Shivering Shovel Search!

episodes.synopsis: Ash and his friends go to a concert starring DJ Leo and his Alolan Dugtrio. Afterwards, they learn that Prof. Kukui and Leo are old friends.
episodes.title: Getting The Band Back Together!

episodes.synopsis: Family Visit Day is approaching at the Pokémon School. Ash is working hard on a speech for the occasion when his mother and Mr. Mime come to visit.
episodes.title: Alolan Open House!

episodes.synopsis: When Team Rocket spy on Ash and Kiawe demonstrating their Z-moves, they're determined to find their own Z-crystals. But Team Skull wants them too!
episodes.title: A Team-On-Team Tussle!

episodes.synopsis: Sophocles learns his family may be moving away. He's sad about leaving his friends at the Pokémon School, and so is his Togedemaru.
episodes.title: So Long, Sophocles!

episodes.synopsis: A mysterious trainer with a powerful Lycanroc easily defeats Team Skull, and rumors about him spread. Then Lillie reveals that he's her brother!
episodes.title: A Glaring Rivalry!

episodes.synopsis: Ash and his friends are ecstatic when the famous Pokébase player and Pokémon School graduate 'Olu'olu comes to umpire a class game of Pokébase.
episodes.title: Pulling Out the Pokémon Base Pepper!

episodes.synopsis: Students and Pokémon take a camping trip together. After they wake up feeling mysteriously drained, they realize there's something in the forest.
episodes.title: Lulled To La-La Land!

episodes.synopsis: Ash and his friends switch Pokémon for two days for a class assignment. Ash takes Snowy to his house while Pikachu goes home with Lillie.
episodes.title: The Ol’ Raise And Switch!

episodes.synopsis: The Akala Island Kahuna Olivia, comes to the Pokémon School. Ash and the rest of the class head to Akala for a practical class under her supervision.
episodes.title: The Island Whisperer!

episodes.synopsis: For the first class on Akala, Ash and his friends are paired with Stoutlands for a treasure hunt. Lillie and Lana struggle with their partners.
episodes.title: Treasure Hunt, Akala Style!

episodes.synopsis: Ash and Lana go Pokémon-fishing in a lagoon famous for a certain type of Pokémon. Meanwhile, Kiawe takes everyone else to his family's farm.
episodes.title: Big Sky, Small Fry!

episodes.synopsis: The students go to the Wela Fire Festival, but before their Pokémon can take turns wearing the Wela Crown, a wild Marowak appears and steals it!
episodes.title: A Crowning Moment Of Truth!

episodes.synopsis: Making traditional Akala curry requires special ingredients. To get everything on their list, Ash and Mallow face wild Pokémon and more.
episodes.title: Currying Favor And Flavor!

episodes.synopsis: At long last, Ash battles Olivia in the Akala Island Grand Trial Challenge. Ash's Rowlet and Rockruff face Olivia's Lycanroc and Probopass!
episodes.title: Trials And Determinations!

episodes.synopsis: The night of the battle, Rockruff sneaks off and meets the island guardian Tapu Lele. The next day, the whole school searches for him.
episodes.title: Rising From The Ruins!

episodes.synopsis: After Team Rocket loses a battle against Ash and Kiawe, Jessie and Mimikyu land in a shopping mall, but Mimikyu's disguise is damaged.
episodes.title: Mimikyu Unmasked!

episodes.synopsis: Feeling unappreciated at her family restaurant, Mallow runs away. While her friends and Team Rocket search for her, she meets an Oranguru.
episodes.title: Mallow And The Forest Teacher!

episodes.synopsis: Lana and Popplio are working on their Z-move, but without much success. When performer Ida and her Brionne visit, Lana asks to train with her.
episodes.title: Balloons, Brionne, And Belligerence!

episodes.synopsis: Sophocles asks Ash and Kiawe to join his team in the annual experimental Charjabug car competition. But Team Rocket also has their eyes on the prize.
episodes.title: Mounting An Electrifying Charge!

episodes.synopsis: When the Pokémon School visits Kanto, Ash reunites with his old friends Misty and Brock and with his old Pokémon! But Team Rocket is back too.
episodes.title: Alola, Kanto!

episodes.synopsis: It's just like old times when Ash and his friends battle Misty and Brock at the Cerulean Gym, with Z-moves versus Mega Evolution.
episodes.title: When Regions Collide!

episodes.synopsis: After returning to Melemele Island, Ash has a strange dream. Then he and his friends find an unknown Pokémon in the forest, and Lillie's mom visits!
episodes.title: A Dream Encounter!

episodes.synopsis: Cosmog goes to school with Ash, where Team Rocket have parked their donut truck. They scheme to steal Cosmog, but it's got teleportation powers.
episodes.title: Now You See Them, Now You Don’t!

episodes.synopsis: Lillie's mom invites everyone to her private island, but her assistant Faba is being creepy towards Cosmog, and Team Rocket has infiltrated the staff!
episodes.title: Deceiving Appearances!

episodes.synopsis: When Ash starts thinking about Lillie's brother Gladion during Pokémon bathtime, Cosmog teleports them to Gladion's location: a valley full of Pinsirs!
episodes.title: A Masked Warning!

episodes.synopsis: Lillie argues with her mother over recording her activities, casting a shadow over the group sleepover at Ash's house with Professor Burnet.
episodes.title: Night of a Thousand Poses!

episodes.synopsis: Following the incident in the cave, Lillie regresses and can't touch Pokémon again. Gladion initially blames Ash, but then starts to suspect Faba.
episodes.title: Mission: Total Recall!

episodes.synopsis: Undeterred, Faba hatches a plan to kidnap Cosmog and use it to open a wormhole to Ultra Space. Lillie, Ash and the crew are hot on his heels!
episodes.title: Faba's Revenge!

episodes.synopsis: While Ash worries about Cosmoem, Lillie and Gladion decide to rescue their mother. To get to Ultra Space, they must find the Guardians on Poni Island.
episodes.title: Family Determination!

episodes.synopsis: Ash and his friends commune with the Island Guardians, who brought Cosmog to him. Professor Kukui heads to Poni Island to help Professor Burnet.
episodes.title: Revealing The Stuff Of Legend!

episodes.synopsis: After arriving in Ultra Space using Solgaleo's power, Lillie and the gang find Lusamine, but she's merged with the Nihilego that kidnapped her!
episodes.title: Rescuing The Unwilling!

episodes.synopsis: Lusamine's possessed Pokémon fight desperately. While Ash, Pikachu and Solgaleo attempt to pin her down, Lillie confronts Lusamine in person.
episodes.title: 10,000,000 Reasons To Fight!

episodes.synopsis: After everyone arrives back at the Pokémon School, Solgaleo vanishes, causing Ash to mope. Professors Kukui and Burnet have an important announcement.
episodes.title: The Professors' New Adventure!

episodes.synopsis: The Pokémon School's Komala drops into a lesson on Pokémon battling. After a Jigglypuff appears, it picks a fight with Komala.
episodes.title: Let Sleeping Pokémon Lie!

episodes.synopsis: When Ash and the professors leave Rotom in charge of the house, it accidentally switches places with the Rotom in a new washing machine!
episodes.title: The Dex Can'T Help It!

episodes.synopsis: James' Mareanie spoils his attempts to catch a Frillish and capture a Toxapex with whom he has a tortured past.
episodes.title: Fighting Back The Tears!

episodes.synopsis: Lana's little sisters return from a walk in the forest with an unusual berry, which Mallow recognizes from when she and Lana were young.
episodes.title: Tasting The Bitter With The Sweet!

episodes.synopsis: The class takes a trip to Ula'ula Island to learn about Alolan ice-type Pokémon along with Kahuna Hala, where they're introduced to Poké-sledding.
episodes.title: Getting A Jump On The Competition!

episodes.synopsis: A wormhole from Ultra Space opens on Melemele Island, and the Ultra Guardians receive their first assignment: stop Buzzwole's rampage!
episodes.title: A Mission Of Ultra Urgency!

episodes.synopsis: Team Rocket mistakes an Alolan Meowth for their Meowth. The new Meowth goes back to their base and seems to be planning to take over Meowth's life.
episodes.title: Acting True To Form!

episodes.synopsis: Ash and Litten watch Masked Royal's latest Battle Royale on TV, then decide to accept his open challenge, along with their friends.
episodes.title: Pushing The Fiery Envelope!

episodes.synopsis: Pokémon School's star alum Ilima comes back for a visit with his Eevee, and Ash tries Poké Diving. But Team Skull interrupts his match with Ilima!
episodes.title: Turning Heads And Training Hard!

episodes.synopsis: The class tries Poké Ping-Pong after a lecture from Ilima, then attends his tournament. Ilima is looking for a rematch, and Team Rocket has plans too.
episodes.title: Smashing With Sketch!

episodes.synopsis: The Poipole returns, and only Pikachu spots it! While Ash and his friends search for Pikachu, Team Rocket start hunting for Poipole to kidnap it.
episodes.title: Love At First Twirl!

episodes.synopsis: A battle with Team Skull nearly makes Ash late for work experience day. The class takes over running the Pokémon Center for Nurse Joy, who has a cold.
episodes.title: Real Life…Inquire Within!

episodes.synopsis: Sophocles finds a buried rocket ship while out camping in a bamboo forest. He assume it's from a fairy tale, but it may be an Ultra Beast!
episodes.title: Rise And Shine, Starship!

episodes.synopsis: Resort executive Bourgain offers to buy Kiawe's family farm, and he won't take no for an answer. To end his sabotage, Kiawe and Marowak challenge him.
episodes.title: The Young Flame Strikes Back!

episodes.synopsis: After a group of Dewpider are forced out of their home, one of them gets separated from the rest. When it meets Lana, it develops a crush on her!
episodes.title: Dewpider Ascending!

episodes.synopsis: Mallow's big brother Ulu and his Lickitung return from their journey just in time for the Alola Bread Festival, and they decide to enter it together!
episodes.title: Sours For The Sweet!

episodes.synopsis: Giovanni tells Team Rocket to head to Ula'ula Island to see the Island King about a Z-ring. There they meet a legendary troublemaker named Gengar.
episodes.title: Why Not Give Me A Z-Ring Sometime?

episodes.synopsis: Prof. Kukui tells the class a Pokémon League may form in Alola and Ash heads to Ula'ula Island for Island Trials with Nanu, Giovanni's old friend.
episodes.title: Tough Guy Trials!

episodes.synopsis: After their defeat by Nanu, Ash and Lycanroc want to grow stronger. Acerola suggests seeking out the Island Guardian, Tapu Bulu.
episodes.title: Some Kind Of Laziness!

episodes.synopsis: Now that Team Rocket have a Z-Move, they want to capture Pikachu. Nanu sends them to battle Ash at an abandoned supermarket, with Acerola as judge.
episodes.title: A Battle Hand-Off!

episodes.synopsis: Ash and Lycanroc face off against Nanu and his Dark Pokémon for a rematch in the Island Grand Trial! But Nanu fights with more than just Pokémon.
episodes.title: Guiding An Awakening!

episodes.synopsis: After a presumed Ultra Beast takes the stage at a fireworks festival, the Ultra Guardians are summoned to capture it. Then another one appears.
episodes.title: Twirling With A Bang!

episodes.synopsis: The class travels to the Hokulani Observatory, run by Sophocles' cousin Molayne, to see a Minior Poké-shower, and Poipole makes friends with one.
episodes.title: Showering The World With Love!

episodes.synopsis: A short cut through a cave system turns complicated: Ash and Kiawe get separated from the group and Lillie finds herself challenging a Tyranitar!
episodes.title: Not Caving Under Pressure!

episodes.synopsis: When Ash sees the Revengers about to cheat in a Battle Royal, he and Torracat jump into the ring to fight alongside Masked Royal as the Double Royals.
episodes.title: A Young Royal Flame Ignites!

episodes.synopsis: Professor Kukui assigns the class Pokémon dancing. As students and Pokémon practice their moves, Team Rocket plots to steal a backup dance crew.
episodes.title: All They Want To Do Is Dance Dance!

episodes.synopsis: Faba returns, showing off his latest invention: an incredible shrinking machine. But when it goes haywire, Ash, Sophocles and Lillie get shrunk!
episodes.title: Dummy, You Shrunk The Kids!

episodes.synopsis: Ash and Poipole meet artist Mina and her empathic Ribombee. Poipole begins expressing itself through painting, but then its feelings take a dark turn.
episodes.title: The Shape Of Love To Come!

episodes.synopsis: After practicing vaulting in gym class, the students mistake Ultra Beast Stakataka for a vault box. The Guardians pursue it to Viren's building site!
episodes.title: The Long Vault Home!

episodes.synopsis: The Ultra Guardians and their Ride Pokémon travel to the Pokémon Paradise Resort for some relaxation. But Team Rocket are already on-site with a plan.
episodes.title: I Choose Paradise!

episodes.synopsis: On the eve of a solar eclipse, the adults are strangely exhausted. The Ultra Guardians set out to disperse the clouds to access a giant wormhole.
episodes.title: Filling The Light With Darkness!

episodes.synopsis: With a mysterious attacker draining the Alola's region's Ultra Aura, the Guardians fight it off with Solgaleo's help.
episodes.title: Full Moon And Many Arms!

episodes.synopsis: The Guardians find Poipole's original home and learn from Ultra Beast Naganadel that Necrozma, who they know as UB Black, was once the Blinding One.
episodes.title: The Prism Between Light And Darkness!

episodes.synopsis: At the height of the eclipse, island kahunas, humans and Pokémon alike lend their energy to Necrozma. Working together, they turn back the darkness!
episodes.title: Securing The Future!

episodes.synopsis: Ash, Kiawe and Mimo visit Pikachu Valley and meet Pika-expert Pikala. Everyone learns a lot about Pikachu and Ash's Pikachu makes lots of new friends.
episodes.title: A Plethora of Pikachu!

episodes.synopsis: Kukui gets roped into taking Burnet and Ash to a Masked Royal meetup at the mall. To keep his secret safe, Kukui asks for Molayne’s help.
episodes.title: Turning the Other Mask!

episodes.synopsis: Ash and his friends perform in the Pokémon School’s play, which takes an unexpected turn as an intruder overtakes the stage. Can they save the play?
episodes.title: Lillier and the Staff!

episodes.synopsis: The Pokémon School becomes a haunted house! While Harper and Sarah are excited to see the Ghost-type Pokémon, something mysterious suddenly happens.
episodes.title: A Haunted House for Everyone!

episodes.synopsis: The Ultra Guardians are on a mission to find out what’s causing the strange magnetic force around Wela Volcano. But watch out for the enraged Golem!
episodes.title: Sparking Confusion!

episodes.synopsis: Ash’s visit to Aether Paradise ends up as a search for Stufful. Someone has to find it before a stranger lays a hand on the adorable-looking Pokémon!
episodes.title: Don't Ignore the Small Stufful!

episodes.synopsis: Ash and Rowlet are challenged to a battle by a friend they meet in the forest. After being so easily defeated, they're determined to win the rematch.
episodes.title: No Stone Unturned!

episodes.synopsis: Rotom is offered a role in a popular TV series, but the shooting will take place overseas. While Ash is happy for Rotom, he is sad to say goodbye.
episodes.title: Bright Lights, Big Changes!

episodes.synopsis: Desperate for friends, a lonely Eevee sets out on an adventure to Alola, but the journey isn't easy. Will Eevee get there safely and find a new home?
episodes.title: We Know Where You're Going, Eevee!

episodes.synopsis: Ash and Pikachu challenge Tapu Koko to a battle and suddenly end up elsewhere. Where are they and how do they get home? And what's this huge Pokémon?
episodes.title: Battling the Beast Within!

episodes.synopsis: The Pokémon School is in destruction, completely ruined! It's up to Ash and Pikachu to make things right or they'll never see their friends again.
episodes.title: Parallel Friendships!

episodes.synopsis: Ash and friends are excited by Brock and Misty's surprise visit and decide to go to Treasure Island for some fun. But it looks like they have company.
episodes.title: Alola, Alola!

episodes.synopsis: Love is in the air! Brock suggests a trip to Akala Island, hoping to see his crush, Olivia, and win her heart. But first, he must pass Olivia's test.
episodes.title: Heart of Fire, Heart of Stone!

episodes.synopsis: For their research projects, Ash and his classmates visit Poni Island, where Ash is accused of stealing Poni Radishes. Can Ash prove his innocence?
episodes.title: That's Some Spicy Island Research!

episodes.synopsis: Ash wants to face Tapu Fini for the Grand Trial and challenges Hapu to a battle, but she only says no. If she's not up for it, maybe someone else is?
episodes.title: Showdown on Poni Island!

episodes.synopsis: In hopes of evolving his Charjabug, Sophocles goes to Vast Poni Canyon, only to have an unexpected encounter with his rivals and enter into a battle.
episodes.title: Evolving Research!

episodes.synopsis: Ash and Kiawe challenge each other when a mysterious old man appears before them. Kiawe must complete his quest in time or Ash's life is in danger.
episodes.title: Run, Heroes, Run!

episodes.synopsis: Ash and friends are helping Hapu on the farm when strange mist suddenly starts to form around them. Could this be the mist they've been talking about?
episodes.title: Memories in the Mist!

episodes.synopsis: Upon becoming the kahuna of Poni Island, Hapu accepts Ash's challenge to the Grand Trial. Which Pokémon will he choose? Will he earn a new Z-Crystal?
episodes.title: A Grand Debut!

episodes.synopsis: A famous Pokémon golfer, who is dismayed by her recent performance, arrives at Alola and ends up giving Ash and friends an unforgettable golf lesson.
episodes.title: Keeping Your Eyes on the Ball!

episodes.synopsis: Ash and his friends realize they had brought with them uninvited guests from Poni Island. These amazing creatures are like nothing ever seen before!
episodes.title: Show Me the Metal!

episodes.synopsis: Professor Oak confirms the mysterious Pokémon's identity! But even before the class has time to get to know them, one of them is already in trouble.
episodes.title: Got Meltan?

episodes.synopsis: Ash and his friends are given a chance to watch a film shoot, where they get to meet an adorable Magikarp named Karpy. But something seems strange.
episodes.title: This Magik Moment!

episodes.synopsis: Oh no! An Ultra Beast has stolen Hala's Z-Crystal! The Ultra Guardians must stop this Ultra Beast named Pheromosa before more Z-Crystals go missing.
episodes.title: Beauty Is Only Crystal Deep!

episodes.synopsis: At last, everyone is excited at the announcement of the Alola Pokémon League except for one person, who's determined to bring down the Pokémon League.
episodes.title: The Dealer of Destruction!

episodes.synopsis: Lillie and Gladion search their father’s old room for any clues to his whereabouts, and Lillie finds his Z-Ring and Magearna, an inactive Pokémon.
episodes.title: The Secret Princess!

episodes.synopsis: Ash and his friends are having a great time at Malie City when Shaymin, Sandy, and Meltan go missing. But wait, is that Team Rocket after the Pokémon?
episodes.title: Drawn with the Wind!

episodes.synopsis: It’s a battle day with the ninjas at Malie City's Gym. Only the finalist gets to battle with the chief on the top floor for the Kantonian Gym badge.
episodes.title: Aiming for the Top Floor!

episodes.synopsis: Sophocles enters a Vikavolt Race to earn a Buginium Z, but it won't be an easy competition. Will he be able to stay strong and earn the first prize?
episodes.title: A High-Speed Awakening!

episodes.synopsis: The Legendary Pokémon Kyogre has been poisoned, and evil Pokémon hunters are after it. Ash and his friends need to save Kyogre before it’s too late!
episodes.title: The One That Didn’t Get Away!

episodes.synopsis: Mallow visits Oranguru's cafe to get some Big Mushrooms, and ends up cooking a unique dish for an unexpected customer, which earns her a special gift.
episodes.title: A Recipe for Success!

episodes.synopsis: Team Rocket’s headquarters wants Bewear, but the truth is, Team Rocket hasn’t caught it. So they come up with a plan of their own to cover up the lie.
episodes.title: Spying for the Big Guy!

episodes.synopsis: Everyone is training hard for the Alola Pokémon League and Sophocles has trouble mastering his Z-Move. Frustrated and upset, he just wants to give up.
episodes.title: A Fiery Training Camp Trick!

episodes.synopsis: There have been mysterious things happening all over Melemele Island lately, and the Ultra Guardians are on the case. But here comes a bigger problem!
episodes.title: Living on the Cutting Edge!

episodes.synopsis: While training for the Alola Pokémon League, a Celebi sends Ash and his Pokémon to the past, where they meet a young boy for some unforgettable fun.
episodes.title: A Timeless Encounter!

episodes.synopsis: Ash and Torracat return from the past and reunite with other Pokémon, only to find them all covered in dirt! What happened while the two were gone?
episodes.title: Pikachu’s Exciting Adventure!

episodes.synopsis: Lillie introduces her friends to a companion who is frozen in time, while Gladion is on a quest to track down a long-lost Pokémon.
episodes.title: Chasing Memories, Creating Dreams!

episodes.synopsis: Ash and his friends eagerly arrive at Manalo Stadium. But when Team Skull causes a ruckus outside, a fight breaks out before the games even begin.
episodes.title: League Offenders and Defenders!

episodes.synopsis: The countdown's in motion as over a hundred Pokémon trainers battle to become the final 16 standing. Dust, fire and lightning fill the air!
episodes.title: Battle Royal 151!

episodes.synopsis: The stadium heats up as the Top 16 face one another: Ash vs. Faba, Ilima vs. Guzma, Hau vs. Principal Oak and Mallow vs. Lana!
episodes.title: Battling Besties!

episodes.synopsis: Jessie and James face off, still undercover and in agreement to perform half-heartedly. But as the fight drags on, one of them changes their mind.
episodes.title: The Battlefield of Truth and Love!

episodes.synopsis: Ash lets Rowlet compete in the next match, but they may not be able to win unless Rowlet masters a new skill in a very short time.
episodes.title: Imitation is the Sincerest Form of Strategy!

episodes.synopsis: It's a close call between Ash and Hau as their Pokémon soar and light up the sky. Rowlet and Decidueye battle it out in the air!
episodes.title: Battling on the Wing!

episodes.synopsis: Some rivals bring out the best in each other, while others trigger the worst. With a spot in the semifinals at stake, Guzma fights dirty.
episodes.title: The Road to the Semifinals!

episodes.synopsis: Kiawe's sister Mimo arrives on the island to cheer him on, but she runs into Team Skull before she reaches the stadium. Luckily, a hero appears!
episodes.title: The Final Four!

episodes.synopsis: The semifinal round begins with Gladion and Silvally facing Kiawe and Turtonator. Then Ash and Torracat square off against Guzma and Scizor.
episodes.title: Getting Down to the Ire!

episodes.synopsis: With his winning streak at stake, Guzma is tormented by fear. But for the first time in a while, he chooses to stay in the fight until the very end.
episodes.title: The Wisdom Not to Run!

episodes.synopsis: Professor Oak and Delia arrive the night before the final match. A group of wild Meltan also come to visit, and with their help, Meltan evolves!
episodes.title: Final Rivals!

episodes.synopsis: As the final match continues, Ash and Pikachu battle against Gladion and Zoroark, with both sides using their Z-moves. There can only be one winner!
episodes.title: Enter the Champion!

episodes.synopsis: As the tournament ends, an Ultra Wormhole opens up, releasing a Guzzlord. When more Ultra Beasts arrive, it's all hands on deck to save the islands.
episodes.title: Z-Move Showdown!

episodes.synopsis: Ash, Alola's first-ever champion, steps into the stadium to battle the legendary Masked Royal, Professor Kukui, in a full six on six match.
episodes.title: Exhibition Unmasked!

episodes.synopsis: The match between Ash and Prof. Kukui continues, with Ash and his friends giving it their all against Kukui's age and experience.
episodes.title: A Full Battle Bounty!

episodes.synopsis: Only three Pokémon remain on each side, and the battle gets even more fiery as it gets down to the wire and both Ash and Kukui deploy their Z-moves.
episodes.title: Fiery Surprises!

episodes.synopsis: In an unexpected twist, Tapu Koko enters the ring as Kukui's final Pokémon against Ash and Naganadel, sparking the ultimate Z-move battle.
episodes.title: From Z to Shining Z!

episodes.synopsis: With a few days left until vacation, Ash and Kiawe duke it out for the first time. Lillie’s attempt to awaken Magearna stirs up memories of her past.
episodes.title: Dreaming of the Sun And Moon!

episodes.synopsis: Led by Magearna's vision, Lillie and Gladion set off on a journey to find their father. Meanwhile, Ash also has plans to depart on his own.
episodes.title: Thank You, Alola! The Journey Continues!
